==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Granulated
<hw>Gran"u*la`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of, or
resembling, grains; crystallized in grains; granular; <as>as,
<ex>granulated</ex> sugar</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having numerous small elevations, as
shagreen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Granulated steel</b></col>, <cd>a variety of steel made
by a particular process beginning with the granulation of pig
iron.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Granulation</ent>⟦br⟧
